stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> FREE
    FREE --> REQUESTED: caller builds lock request
    REQUESTED --> SHARD_LOCKED: acquire LockManager shard

    SHARD_LOCKED --> GRANTED: compatible
    SHARD_LOCKED --> WAITING: conflict, enqueue and add wait edge

    GRANTED --> CONVERTING: upgrade requested
    CONVERTING --> GRANTED: conversion compatible
    CONVERTING --> WAITING: conversion conflict

    WAITING --> GRANTED: granted after blocker releases
    WAITING --> TIMEOUT: wait deadline reached
    WAITING --> VICTIM: deadlock detector selects transaction

    GRANTED --> RELEASED: statement or transaction release
    TIMEOUT --> RELEASED: remove waiting request and wait edges
    VICTIM --> RELEASED: rollback cleanup releases owned locks
    RELEASED --> FREE
    FREE --> [*]

    note right of WAITING
        Only transaction logical locks enter Wait-For Graph.
        Caller must not hold page latch, file latch, undo page latch,
        Buffer Pool list lock, or RecordCursor while waiting.
    end note

    note right of GRANTED
        Ownership belongs to TransactionLockSet.
        RecordCursor and PageHandle do not own transaction locks.
    end note

